FBIS4-50709 "drchi098_p_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-098 Daily Report 13 May 1994 Central-South Region Price Increases Reportedly Slower in Guangzhou Price Increases Reportedly Slower in Guangzhou HK1905145494 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in Mandarin 1000 GMT 13 May 94 HK1905145494 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] Price hikes in the city of Guangzhou are slowing down somewhat. According to statistics, in April this year, the city's general level of retail prices and general level of wholesale prices were 17.5 and 21 percent higher respectively than the same period last year. However, compared with March this year, the margins of increase were 3.7 and 4.6 percent lower respectively. The main reason why price hikes in April slowed somewhat is that the government has adopted relevant measures to curb price increases.
